article.headline: Wright St. 61, Detroit 59
article.story: DETROIT -- Vaughn Duggins scored 17 points, including two crucial free throws in the final minute, and Wright State held on to defeat Detroit 61-59 Saturday. Todd Brown added 16 points for the Raiders (12-8, 5-4 Horizon), who led 35-26 at halftime. Wright State led 58-47 after a Brown 3-pointer with 2:58 remaining. Detroit (12-8, 5-4) then began its comeback, with 3-pointers by Xavier Keeling and Woody Payne cutting the deficit to five points a minute later. Keeling's layup with a minute to play made it 58-55 and Payne's free throw got the Titans within two. Duggins' free throws made the lead four points, but Chase Simon's 3-pointer with 22 seconds left cut the Raiders' lead to 60-59. Cory Cooperwood made a free throw with 19 seconds left, and Detroit missed a pair of shots at the end. Simon led the Titans with 15 points and Keeling scored 12.
